    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-squash-stew-with-parsnip-sweet-potato-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and <strong>garlic </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-squash-stew-with-parsnip-sweet-potato-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your<strong> mince</strong> to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and increase the heat to high</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-squash-stew-with-parsnip-sweet-potato-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> roughly</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in<span class=\"text-purple\"> </span>300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[400ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Once your mince has browned, add the<strong> chopped mushrooms </strong>and<strong> </strong>your <strong>butternut squash cubes </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-squash-stew-with-parsnip-sweet-potato-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 1-2 min, add the <strong>stock</strong>, your<strong> Dijon mustard</strong> and your <strong>Hendersons' relish</strong> with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook, covered, for 20-25 min or until the sauce has reduced, the squash has softened and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> mince & squash stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-squash-stew-with-parsnip-sweet-potato-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the stew is cooking, peel your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and <strong>parsnip[s] </strong>and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong> and <strong>parsnip</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-squash-stew-with-parsnip-sweet-potato-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the cooked potato and parsnip to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>parsnip mash</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lean-beef-and-squash-stew-with-parsnip-sweet-potato-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> mince & squash stew</strong> with the <strong>parsnip mash</strong> to the side</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
